<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="442" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/978a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-14T19:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Cable Department whether Ecuadoran Government is continuing to make
                                deposits on interest on railroad bonds and how much it has deposited
                                up to date. Have any remittances been made to London? Also advise
                                Department where money is deposited and under what conditions, and
                                whether money can be withdrawn, if so desired, by Government of
                                Ecuador.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>